FPAT
====

FPAT is a Framework for Program Analysis and Transformation.

Requirements
------------

* OCaml 4.03.0 or later (http://www.caml.org)
* OPAM 1.22 or later (http://opam.ocamlpro.com/)

Required OPAM packages
----------------------

* ocamlfind
* extlib
* zarith
* camlp4
* camlp5

Optional OPAM packages
----------------------

* minisat (http://www.dcs.gla.ac.uk/~michele/camlminisat.html)
* apron
* ocaml-glpk
* gsl
* cil
* llvm

Further Options
---------------

* Z3 4.4.2.1 (https://github.com/Z3Prover/z3/)
* CVC3 (http://www.cs.nyu.edu/acsys/cvc3/)
* CSIsat 1.2 (http://www.sosy-lab.org/~dbeyer/CSIsat/)
* RSRefine (https://bitbucket.org/terauchi/idepceg)
* AiSatClone

* GSL CQP extension (http://www.network-theory.co.uk/download/gslextras/Bundle/)
* SPPoC (http://www.lifl.fr/west/sppoc/)
* OSDP (https://cavale.enseeiht.fr/osdp/)

Installation
------------

First, edit "Makefile.config.model" and save it as "Makefile.config".
Then, run the following commands to build and install FPAT:

  $ autoconf
  $ ./configure
  $ make install-lib
  $ make
  $ make install

